        <td >
<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=10 width=100%>
<tr>
<td>
<br>
<div align="left" class="article_text">

<!--startscanning-->Anime Expo has proved once again to be the premier industry con each year. Many licenses manga and anime alike, announcements, etc. I will list all of the manga and anime that were licensed, and a description of most titles.<br><br>All in all, about 13 licenses this time around. Not a record, but still very high and a very good sign for the Anime industry as whole as it appears to be slowly crawling out of it's slump and finding moderation.<br><br>Read more for all the information!<br><br><br><br>So far at Anime Expo, the following companies have licensed a variety of titles.<br><br>Anime Licenses:<br><br>ADV has licensed <span style="text-decoration:underline">Nerima Daikon Brothers</span> and has also announced that they will be working on the actual production of <span style="text-decoration:underline">Full Metal Panic! The Second Raid</span> while Funimation would only handle the marketing aspect of the title. They have also licensed <span style="text-decoration:underline">GUYVER: The Bioboosted Armor</span>.<br><br>Funimation has acquired <span style="text-decoration:underline">Glass Fleet</span> and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Solty Rei</span>. They also confirmed that they own the rights to <span style="text-decoration:underline">Witchblade</span>.<br><br>Geneon has announced they licensed <span style="text-decoration:underline">Paradise Kiss</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Black Lagoon</span>, and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Hello Kitty: Stump Village</span>.<br><br>Bandai has announced their license of <span style="text-decoration:underline">Kakuri Kaiden Hiwou Senki</span>, all 3 <span style="text-decoration:underline">Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam: A New Translation</span> movies, and <span style="text-decoration:underline">.hack//Roots</span>.<br><br>The Right Stuf International has licensed the cult title, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Super Gals season 2</span>.<br><br><br>Manga Licenses:<br><br>Dark Horse Manga has licensed <span style="text-decoration:underline">Dame Dame Saito Nikki</span>, and S<span style="text-decoration:underline">atsuma Gishiden</span>.<br><br>Viz Shoujo Beat acquired <span style="text-decoration:underline">Punch!</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Gentleman Alliance</span>, and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Be With You</span>.<br><br>Go!Comi announced <span style="text-decoration:underline">Train+Train</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">After School Nightmare</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Black Sun Silver Moon</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">The Devil Within</span>, and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Night of the Beasts</span>.<br><br>Bandai Manga acquired the original manga adaptation of <span style="text-decoration:underline">Witchblade</span>.<br><br>Tokyopop has licensed <span style="text-decoration:underline">Tatics</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Shinsengumi Immon Peace Maker</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Aqua</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Wild Adapter</span>, and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Gakuen Heaven</span>.<br><br>Seven Seas Entertainment announced the license of <span style="text-decoration:underline">Kaisimasi - Girl Meets Girl</span>, and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Kodomo no Jikan</span>. They also announced <span style="text-decoration:underline">Shinsengumi no Ballad</span> novel.<br><br>Broccoli announced <span style="text-decoration:underline">Galaxy Angel 2</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Kon Kon Kokon</span>, <span style="text-decoration:underline">Disgaea</span> Game Character Collection Artbooks.<br><br><br>Industry News:<br><br>Funimation has announced <span style="text-decoration:underline">Fullmetal Alchemist: Conqueror of Shamballa</span> will be on theater in September 8, and DVD on September 12.<br><br>The Right Stuf International mentioned <span style="text-decoration:underline">To Heart</span> is taking longer than expected due to difficulty remastering the source material.<br><br><br><br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Nerima Daikon Brothers</span> is a 12 episode series by Shinichi Watanabe, the creator of <span style="text-decoration:underline">Excel Saga</span> and <span style="text-decoration:underline">Puni Puni Poemy</span>. This series runs along the same vein as Excel Saga. The story revolves around Hideki, who organizes a band of friends and a panda which resembles a daikon, in order to earn money. They defeat evil guys and take their money with singing, so it's basically a musicial comedy.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Full Metal Panic! The Second Raid</span> is the third series in the <span style="text-decoration:underline">Full Metal Panic</span> franchise. In this third series, things get back to being more on the serious side rather than the comedy of <span style="text-decoration:underline">Fumoffu</span>. It has a lot of mecha combat, the only series where I actually enjoyed it to some extent, and good character development. It's generally a highly recommended franchise for any fan to watch.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Glass Fleet</span> is a highly unrealistic space drama. The outfits and lifestyles are akin to aristocrat European times during the revolution. But it's set in space. It involves a lot of bishounens (pretty boys). It is mostly going to be found appealing by those who enjoy anime such as Meine Liebe. The poor are staging a revolution against the aristocrats.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Solty Rei</span> is about a young girl named Solty, who is a superpowerful Android that has lost her memory and happens to meet a bounty hunter named Revant. The world is a postapocalyptic era where humans and androids look alike. Revant is trying to find the truth about Solty and the government which makes a show of being one of the good guys who try to help others.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Witchblade</span> revolves around a young, well endowed woman who becomes an ancent weapon posessing the sentient weapon, Witchblade. This woman, a police officer, Masane Amou must now fight the forces of evil with it.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Paradise Kiss</span> is a 12 episode series about a honor student, Yukari, who meets a group of students at an art school. When she finds how freely they are living, she begins to feel like she's trapped in a cage. After some convincing, she becomes a model for this group, Paradise Kiss. They help each other achieve their dreams. Based on a classic shoujo manga.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Black Lagoon</span> is a higly anticipated show about Okajima Rokuro, nicknamed Rock, who got abducted for his secret files while travelling. When he finds out his company set out to kill him for the secrets he holds, he has no choice but to join the group of Pirates. She meets Levi, a female mercenary with a dark past and extreme profiency with guns. This follows their eccentric adventures plundering and leaving much destruction in their wake.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">.hack//Roots</span> is a prequel to the <span style="text-decoration:underline">.hack</span> franchise.<br><br><span style="text-decoration:underline">Super Gals</span> S2 is the second season (ep 26-52). It has never been released in Japan, but there is a large cult following in America. It is about three girls in Shibuya who try to teach others how to be a super gal, an empowered woman who respects herself.<!--/startscanning-->

